martini goose dinner switzerland stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff calendar martini goose dinner switzerland go back details november 11 2011 from 6 30 pm 9 00 pm restaurant old swiss house lowenplatz 4 6004 luzern switzerland sls alumni are invited to join the stanford club of switzerland and the stanford business school alumni association swiss chapter for the 9th annual traditional martini goose dinner at restaurant old swiss house the restaurant is owned by the third generation of the buholzer family it is not only well known for its delicious cuisine but also for its outstanding wine cellar with over 30000 bottles it has hosted many celebrities including richard nixon yves st laurent sir simon rattle roger federer and frank sinatra in addition it has a great collection of antiques the cost is chf 120 for general admission chf 60 for members ages 35 and younger incl cocktails & mineral water excl dinner wine & coffee to be paid in cash only at the event space is limited so please register by october 31 a full no show charge will be applied for any cancellations after this date to register please fill out the registration form that may be found under related media related media registration form contact sls alumni relations alumni relations law stanford edu 650.723 2730 related office of external relations cloudy 57 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
